ABUJA – The Emefiele Support Group (ESG) on Saturday congratulated Nigerian Muslims as they commence this year’s Ramadan fast. The group, which is independently advocating the emergence of the Governor of the Central Bank of Nigeria, Dr Godwin Emefiele, as the All Progressives Congress (APC) consensus candidate and next President of Nigeria, called on them to utilise the opportunity offered by the Holy month to pray for peace, progress and unity of the country. The ESG also urged Muslims to continue to support the efforts of the administration of President Muhammadu Buhari meant to reposition the country. The position of ESG was contained in a statement by its Director of Communications, Benigna Ejimba. The statement read: “The Emefiele Support Group (ESG) thanks to the Almighty Allah for giving Muslims in Nigeria the opportunity to join their counterparts across the world to observe this year’s Ramadan fast. “As they embark on this annual spiritual exercise, we urge them to ensure they continue to pray for the peace, growth, progress and unity of our dear country. “We urge them to remain in the forefront of supporting the various efforts of President Buhari’s administration to further reposition this great nation positively. “Above all, we urge them to pray and be committed to ensuring that only a competent person capable of sustaining the legacies of President Buhari and improving on them emerges as the next President through the 2023 general elections. POLL “Let Muslims and indeed all Nigerians embrace peace and shun all forms of violence that are capable of reversing the gains and achievements of the present administration.”